        %span co-founder

      = image_tag 'bradley-kipp.jpg'

      %p Bradley is co-founder at UpHex, his second start-up adventure. He is a reformed banker, having spent four years in investment banking prior to the start-up world. Bradley stumbled into entrepreneurship during his second year at UVA's Darden School of Business when he joined the founding team of Cardagin Networks. At Cardagin, he was in charge of finance, business development, strategy, and operations. 

      %p Bradley holds a BA (cum laude) from Vanderbilt University and an MBA from UVA's Darden School of Business. In his spare time, Bradley enjoys spending time with his wife and two young boys. He also is teaching himself how to code (albeit slowly).

